## 4. The Hand Feel Experience

- Impact Sensation
    - Hardness Words — Medium-hard, crisp, supportive.
    - Feedback — Very clear transmission of the ball impact to the hand.
    - Hold vs. Release — Noticeable hold (dwell) initially, followed by a crisp, energetic release.
    - Dwell Time — Above average, allowing for high-quality spin manipulation.

- Sound/Click
    - Produces a satisfying, moderate click on active loops, though slightly muted compared to non-sticky tensors due to the hybrid top.

